# Phase 6 — Complete Physics System

Current phase: Phase 6.

This phase builds the complete physics integration.

## Allowed dependencies

Existing dependencies plus:

- Jolt Physics

## Required library

Create `hockey_physics`.

Dependency:

```text
hockey_physics -> hockey_core, hockey_ecs
```

## Required features

Implement physics world, fixed timestep simulation, rigid bodies, collider components, triggers, physics materials, collision layers/filtering, raycasts, shape casts if needed, overlaps, debug draw, character/controller support if used, server-safe deterministic-ish settings, scene-to-physics sync, and physics-to-scene sync.

## Required ECS components

Implement and serialize `RigidBodyComponent`, `BoxColliderComponent`, `SphereColliderComponent`, `CapsuleColliderComponent`, `MeshColliderComponent`, `TriggerComponent`, `PhysicsMaterialComponent`, and `CharacterControllerComponent` if used.

## Hockey physics support

Implement puck rigid body, player/goalie capsules, rink board colliders, goal triggers, ice friction material, puck/player materials, and collision layers for player/puck/rink/goal/trigger.

## Required modes

Physics must support authoritative server simulation, client-side prediction physics where needed, editor preview/simulation, and debug visualization.

## Required tests

Create `HockeyPhysicsTests` covering world init/shutdown, rigid body/collider creation, raycast, trigger event, collision event, fixed timestep, puck bounce/friction sanity, scene sync, and debug draw path.

## Definition of done

Phase 6 is complete only when physics builds/tests pass, scene physics components serialize, physics runs fixed timestep, hockey colliders/materials work, editor collider visualization works, and server can run physics headlessly.
